Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy is issued by
Spring Feeling Foods DMCC
, trading as
"Spring,"
and applies to all services provided through our website and mobile app. Protecting your personal information is a priority for us, and this document explains how we collect, use, and protect your data. We encourage you to read it carefully to understand your rights and our responsibilities in managing your information.
1. Who Are We?
Spring Feeling Foods DMCC, part of the Kcal World Group, is headquartered in the United Arab Emirates (UAE). References to "we," "us," or "our" throughout this policy refer to Spring Feeling Foods DMCC. As a UAE-based entity, we comply with the country’s data protection and privacy regulations to ensure your information is handled responsibly.
We operate under the highest standards of transparency and data protection, aligning with both regional regulations and international best practices. Whether you use our website or mobile app, we are committed to delivering a secure and personalized experience.
2. Data We Collect
To provide and improve our services, we collect various types of personal information, including but not limited to:
Personal Identifiers: Name, date of birth, address, phone number, email address, and payment card details.
Account Information: Login credentials such as usernames and passwords.
Service Usage Data: Purchase history, order details, and delivery preferences.
Communication Preferences: Opt-ins for marketing communications and how you engage with them.
Technical Data: Device type, IP address, browser type, and online activity (e.g., cookies and analytics data).
Feedback and Reviews: Any information shared through surveys, customer service channels, or social media interactions.
We aim to collect only the information necessary to deliver and enhance our services effectively.
3. How We Use Your Information
Your data is used in various ways to deliver a smooth, secure, and personalized experience:
Providing Services: Process your payments, deliver orders, and manage your account.
Personalization: Tailor recommendations, promotions, and marketing messages to suit your preferences.
Security: Prevent fraud, secure your data, and ensure safe transactions.
Improvements: Analyze purchase trends, feedback, and app usage to enhance our offerings.
Compliance: Meet legal and regulatory requirements, including fraud prevention.
4. Legal Basis for Processing
We process your personal information based on these legal grounds:
Consent: When you opt in to receive promotional messages or agree to certain terms.
Contractual Obligations: For fulfilling service agreements (e.g., delivering meal kits).
Legitimate Interests: To improve our services, prevent fraud, and personalize marketing.
Legal Obligations: Compliance with laws and regulations.
Where required, we ensure that your explicit consent is obtained before processing sensitive information.
5. How We Protect Your Information
The security of your data is paramount. We implement advanced measures to safeguard it, including:
Restricted access to systems and data for authorized personnel only.
Encryption of sensitive information, such as payment details.
Firewalls, secure servers, and real-time monitoring to prevent unauthorized access.
Routine security audits and adherence to industry standards for data protection.
These measures ensure your information is handled with the utmost care.
6. Sharing Your Information
We may share your personal information under the following circumstances:
Within Kcal World Group: For improved services and tailored promotions across our brands.
Service Providers: With third-party vendors (e.g., payment processors, delivery partners) to facilitate our operations.
Marketing Partners: To provide advertisements aligned with your interests.
Legal Requirements: To comply with regulatory obligations or protect our legal rights.
Business Transfers: If ownership changes, your data will be protected and handled per this policy.
We ensure all third parties adhere to stringent data protection standards.
7. Marketing Communications
We may contact you with promotional offers via email, SMS, WhatsApp, or push notifications. These messages are sent only if you’ve consented or where we have a legitimate interest. You can manage your preferences or unsubscribe by:
Logging into your account and updating settings.
Contacting us at info@springfeeling.com.
We aim to make opting in and out of communications simple and hassle-free.
8. Cookies and Analytics
Cookies and similar technologies help us:
Enhance your browsing experience.
Understand how you use our website and app.
Deliver personalized ads and recommendations.
For a detailed overview, please refer to our Cookie Policy. You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings at any time.
9. Your Rights
You have the following rights regarding your personal data:
Access the information we hold about you.
Request corrections to inaccurate or incomplete data.
Restrict or object to certain data processing activities.
Withdraw consent for marketing communications.
Request deletion of your personal information ("Right to be Forgotten").
To exercise your rights, contact us at info@springfeeling.com. For your security, verification may be required before processing requests.
10. Data Retention
We retain your information only as long as necessary:
For active accounts, until you request deletion through the Spring Portal.
For inactive accounts, up to 7 years for tax and legal compliance, unless a longer period is legally required.
11. Payments and Refunds
Payments made via Visa and MasterCard are securely processed in AED through a certified gateway. Card details are tokenized for recurring transactions. Refunds are issued exclusively to the original payment method and processed within a defined timeframe.
12. Automated Decision-Making
We use automated systems for certain processes, such as:
Personalizing marketing offers.
Detecting and preventing fraudulent transactions.
If automated decisions significantly impact you, you may request human intervention.
13. Changes to This Policy
This Privacy Policy was last updated on
December 1, 2024.
Any updates will be communicated via our website or app. Changes take effect on the date they are posted.
14. Contact Us
